net.proteusframework.core.metric

Class Point

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.core.metric.Point
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public final class Point
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    The Point class is used to specify the position of something. The x and y position are specified using Metric objects so that varying units can be used. Instances of this class are immutable.
    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

      • Point

        public Point(java.lang.String str)
        Creates a Point object from a String. The format is a comma-separated x and y value. The x and y values are in the format defined by Metric.valueOf(String).
        Parameters:
        str - The String representation of the point.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the String does not specify comma separated x and y Metric values.
        java.lang.NumberFormatException - If the decimal values are illegal
        See Also:
        Metric.valueOf(String)
